<title>VENEZUELA: Venezuelan firms see wages up 44 pct in yr - survey.</title>
<headline>Venezuelan firms see wages up 44 pct in yr - survey.</headline>
<dateline>CARACAS 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Venezuelan businesses expects private sector wages to rise an average 44 percent this year, a survey by local business chamber Coindustria showed.</p>
<p>According to the first quarter of 1997 survey, which polled 450 small, medium and large business, seventy five percent of respondents said they would probably raise wages this year.</p>
<p>In April, the government raised the minimum wage 44 percent to 75,000 bolivars ($156) per month.  That rise followed a 70 percent plus public sector pay rise in February.</p>
<p>((-- John Paul Rathbone, Caracas newsroom, 582 505 2600))</p>
